               <msContents>
                  <summary>Images 1r-xxx: Psalter of the Virgin (i.e., with a five-line rhyming hymn mentioning Mary at the conclusion of each Psalm), incomplete at the beginning (illumination). The midpoint of the Psalms in indicated with three full-stop symbols (image 75r). Psalm 151 is the short version. The Song of Songs is the common version. Image 173r, col. 1: excerpt from Angles Praise Her. Image 173r, col. 2-175r: Miracle of Mary regarding Ephrem, the Syrian, as an introduction to the Praises of Mary. Image 195l: Prayer to Jesus Christ, incomplete at the beginning. Illuminations added recently over text. Image 149r mentions the owner, Lǝj ወልደ ማርያም. Image 173 mentions a secondary owner, ተወልደ መድኀን.  Image 194r records a curse on anyone who steals or effaces the book. </summary>
